  "prompt": "What is the average price of a wedding dress?",
  "response": "The average price of a wedding dress can vary widely depending on several factors such as the designer, style, materials, and location. As of recent data, the average cost of a wedding dress in the United States tends to range between $1,500 and $2,300. However, you can find dresses for much less or much more than this range. Off-the-rack dresses or those from larger retail chains can be more affordable, sometimes costing under $500, while designer gowns or custom-made dresses can be significantly more expensive, potentially costing $5,000 or more. Always consider additional costs such as alterations, accessories, and taxes when budgeting for a wedding dress.",
